               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1211" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1211" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1211" type="surname" value="EASTIRBY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1211" type="given" value="GEORGE HENRY FLINTOFT"></interp>GEORGE HENRY FLINTOFT EASTIRBY</persName>
                  </hi>. I lived in George-street, St. Giles's, the prisoner lodged there. On the night of the 17th of January, he slept in another bed at the foot of mine, and went to bed after me—I missed my coat when I was awoke by my landlady crying out, "The old man's coat is stolen off the bed"—it was between one and two o'clock in the day—I had been very afflicted all night, and felt heavy for sleep—this is the coat—this handkerchief was in the pocket</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1212" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1212" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1212" type="surname" value="SANDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1212" type="given" value="MARGARET"></interp>MARGARET SANDS</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the lodging-house—the prisoner lodged there that night—it was the first night—I met him between one and two o'clock on the first landing—I told him to wait a minute while I went to see if all was right—I missed the coat off the bed—I followed him into the mews and took him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1213" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1213" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1213" type="surname" value="POWELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1213" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN POWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I came borne from Covent Garden-market at a quarter-past one o'clock. I heard Mrs. Sands exclaim, "The old man's coat is gone on that man's back"—I followed the prisoner to Clark's-mews, and asked how he came to take the coat—he said he did not care—I took him to the station-house—he had the coat on.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> It was distress made me do it.</p>
